By the time he left office, eight out of 11 boxes were bright red, with North Korea testing missiles and bombs.
With North Korea suspending nuclear and missile tests, other boxes have returned to a more reassuring mid-red or pink.
The risk with North Korea, many experts say, is Trump’s rush to make a deal when talks resume this week.
